HOUSE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 21
BY REPRESENTATIVE HORTON
COMMENDATIONS: Commends John Keith of AllState Land and Timber on being
named Louisiana Outstanding Logger of the Year
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To commend John Keith of AllState Land and Timber on being named Louisiana
3 Outstanding Logger of the Year.
4 WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize John Keith of AllState Land and Timber
5 in Haughton, Louisiana, for his commitment to safe and efficient logging practices; and
6 WHEREAS, Louisiana loggers are integral members of the forest community who
7 move timber from forest land to mills so that it can be processed into useful products;
8 without loggers, the forest industry would not exist, and Louisiana's forests would become
9 overgrown and unproductive; and
10 WHEREAS, logging is traditionally a family-centered industry that is made up of
11 small businesses that utilize family members in their operations; loggers contribute
12 significantly to their respective local economies by purchasing fuel and lubricants and
13 supporting charitable causes and community needs; and
14 WHEREAS, loggers face a number of variables, including inclement weather, market
15 volatility, equipment breakdowns, and labor issues, in their day-to-day operations; these
16 hurdles often lead to demanding work hours, and loggers rely on their family and faith to
17 push them through the day; and
18 WHEREAS, John Keith was selected by his peers as the representation of all that is
19 good about the logging industry; he has long provided the state's forest industry with a vital
20 service delivering timber to processing facilities, and he currently serves as president of the
21 Louisiana Logging Council; and
